@flexiarg stack-coherence/commit-intent-alignment
@title Commit Intent Alignment
@sigils [🌆/上 ➰/升]
@keywords commit, pr, pull-request, drift, reconcile, sync, mismatch, planned, roadmap, progress, git
@audience futon stewards, stack maintainers
@tone analytic-neutral
@factor Energy (viriya)
@references [stack-coherence/staleness-scan stack-coherence/ready-blocked-triage devmap-coherence/next-steps-to-done]

! conclusion: 
  correlate commit messages/PRs with devmap IDs; for each match, update the clause status + evidence ledger; if a clause stays marked “planned” despite recent commits, flag it as `drift` and prompt someone to reconcile

  + context: You need to ensure that actual development work reflected in commits and PRs stays aligned with work plans as both code and plans evolve.

  + IF:
    git commits reference a prototype or futon clause (“Prototype 4 done”, “stack blocker cleared”) while the devmap still lists it as planned/blocked

  + HOWEVER:
    that disconnect makes the roadmap lie about where energy went

  + THEN:
    correlate commit messages/PRs with devmap IDs; for each match, update the clause status + evidence ledger; if a clause stays marked “planned” despite recent commits, flag it as `drift` and prompt someone to reconcile

  + BECAUSE:
    viriya is kinetic practice—commits and devmaps must reflect the same movement or we lose trust in both

  + NEXT-STEPS:
    next[Add a nightly scan that correlates commits/PRs with devmap IDs and updates evidence.]
    next[Flag any clause still marked planned after matching commits for reconciliation.]
